We have [clear guidelines in ADG|https://developer.atlassian.com/design/latest/language.html] that dictate how capitalisation should be handled in our products.

{quote}
Sentence case for everything but titles.
{quote}

This is one area that JIRA is yet to embrace. The motivation for wanting this is that as a developer, it would be great to have clear existing examples of "how to do it", so that those that aren't intimately familiar with the ADG guidelines have a chance to _get it right_.

[According to Wikipedia|http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Proper_noun]:

{quote}
A proper noun is a noun that in its primary application refers to a unique entity, such as London, Jupiter, Sarah, or Microsoft, as distinguished from a common noun, which usually refers to a class of entities (city, planet, person, corporation),
{quote}

The way I see it is that everything that's a title or proper noun should be title case, and everything else should be sentence case.

